The paper discusses reinforcement learning (RL) applied to interactive recommender systems (IRS), which involves learning from dynamic interactions and planning for long-run performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
